- `pkg/analysis/workstream.go` (blocked detection)
- `pkg/ui/labeldashboard.go` (warning UI)
- `pkg/ui/styles.go` (warning styles)

Expand the label view to include upstream dependencies (blockers) of labeled issues.

## Requirements
- Given a set of labeled issues, traverse upstream to find all blocking issues
- Default depth: 3 levels of dependencies
- Configurable depth via `d` key (cycle 1 â†’ 2 â†’ 3 â†’ All â†’ 1)
- Direction: upstream (blockers) by default
- Mark expanded issues distinctly from directly-labeled issues

## Algorithm
```
func expandDependencies(labeledIssues []Issue, depth int) []Issue {
    seen := map[string]bool{}
    queue := labeledIssues  // BFS from labeled issues

    for level := 0; level < depth; level++ {
        nextQueue := []Issue{}
        for _, issue := range queue {
            for _, dep := range issue.Dependencies {
                if !seen[dep.ID] {
                    seen[dep.ID] = true
                    nextQueue = append(nextQueue, dep)
                }
            }
        }
        queue = nextQueue
    }

    return allDiscoveredIssues
}
```

## Data Model
- Track whether each issue is "primary" (has label) or "context" (pulled in via deps)
- Store current depth setting in view state

## Files to modify
- `pkg/ui/labeldashboard.go` (add expansion logic)
- `pkg/analysis/` (may add helper for dependency traversal)
- Consider reusing graph traversal from existing analysis code

Group labels by detected prefixes in the label selector UI.

## Requirements
- Auto-detect common prefixes from existing labels
- Group labels hierarchically by prefix
- Collapsible prefix groups
- Allow user override via config

## Auto-Detection Algorithm
```go
func detectLabelGroups(labels []string) map[string][]string {
    delimiters := []string{":", "/", "-", "_"}
    prefixCounts := map[string]int{}

    for _, label := range labels {
        for _, delim := range delimiters {
            if idx := strings.Index(label, delim); idx > 0 {
                prefix := label[:idx+1]  // include delimiter
                prefixCounts[prefix]++
                break
            }
        }
    }

    // Keep prefixes that appear 2+ times
    groups := map[string][]string{}
    for prefix, count := range prefixCounts {
        if count >= 2 {
            groups[prefix] = filterByPrefix(labels, prefix)
        }
    }

    return groups
}
```

